							<p><b>BOOST</b> stands for  <b>B</b>usiness perf<b>O</b>rmance impr<b>O</b>vement through individual employee <b>S</b>kills <b>T</b>raining. A technical prototype, that used to organise, manage and monitor training process in the small and micro enterprises.</p>
							<p> Below are a few steps to help you get started.</p>

				            <ul style="padding: 10px;">
				            	<li><b>If you are a Manager:</b> 
				            		<ul style="padding: 10px;">
				            			<li>Assign user roles to employees and trainers using the <b>Access Rights</b> widget.</li>
				            			<li>Define business goals and add learning indicators to them using the <b>Business Goals</b> widget. Assign priority to the goals, specifying the most improtant with a high priority.</li>
					               	  	<li>Monitor business goals progress and employees competence in the <b>Learning Progress</b> widget. It works together with <b>Business Goals</b> and <b>Business Employees</b> widgets. </li>
					                	<li>Edit information about employees and assign goals to them, adjust their learning levels in the <b>Business Employees</b> widget.</li>
					              	</ul>
					            </li>
					            <li><b>If you are an Employee: </b>
				            		<ul style="padding: 10px;">
					                	<li>Use a <b>Boost Search</b> widget to Ô¨Ånd learning materials.</li> 
					               	  	<li>Watch and read interesting resources using <b>Boost Viewer</b> widget.</li>
					                	<li>Save and organise your learning resources in the <b>Learning Repository:</b>. You can review and add new learning documents, experts and widgets assigned to the goal and learning indicators.</li>
					              		<li>Monitor your learning progress with the <b>Learning Progress</b> widget.</li>
					              	</ul>
					            </li>
					            <li><b>If you are a Trainer: </b>  
				            		<ul style="padding: 10px;">
					                	<li>Provide access to the learning repositories in the <b>Boost Search</b> widget.</li> 
					               	  	<li>Add description to learning indicators in the <b>Business Goals</b> widget.</li> 
					               	  	<li>Adjust learning levels of employees in the <b>Business Employees</b> widget.</li> 
					              	</ul>
				            	</li>
				            </ul> 
				            <p>We hope this Quick Start has been helpful in showing you how to get started using BOOST quickly and easily. 
